  "manufacturing_orders_comment": "Curated real subset from Jadwal Produksi Warping Dasar.csv (352-row warping schedule export). mo_id/dates/lembar/sc(=Sales Contract, from source)/order_per_beam_m are taken directly from the source; lot(=yarn production batch from the yarn factory, used to keep same-batch yarn together to avoid dye/shade defects) is NOT in the source export and is a randomly generated placeholder code here — one sc can span multiple MOs (see MO260700727/MO260700729), while lot identifies the physical cheese/batch and must match exactly for two loads to be considered interchangeable. denier is back-calculated where the source had real weight+length data (denier = weight_kg*9,000,000/(lembar*length_m)), else read off the product code. knitting_mc repurposed to carry the CSV's 'Dept Tujuan' (JACQUARD/TRICOT) since the real export has no downstream knitting-machine number.",
